message: Reverted [[WP:AGF|good faith]] edits by [[Special:Contributions/Jhobbs02|Jhobbs02]] ([[User talk:Jhobbs02|talk]]): Already linked above in same paragraph.

I understand the reason for not explaining what this is in the opening sentence, but the altered text violates [[WP:EASTEREGG]] and wrongly implies that "kami no michi" is actually a widely used alternative name for the religion. If a correct classification of this reading would be too confusing to readers to be included in the opening sentence, the reading itself probably shouldn't be included in the opening sentence.
